      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Inside a heavy nucleus, an alpha particle is trapped in a deep nuclear well. Outside sits a tall hill of electric repulsion: the Coulomb barrier.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Classically, an alpha particle with less energy than the hill cannot escape. Its energy line never reaches the top, so the classical answer is an eternal prison.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.51,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Quantum mechanically, its wavefunction leaks through the forbidden region. A tiny tail survives beyond the barrier, so each collision with the wall carries a tiny escape probability.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "decay"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.56,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "Tiny is not zero. Repeated attempts turn that tunneling probability into a measurable decay rate.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "pulse"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.4,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The key is exponential sensitivity. The transmission probability is an exponential of a large negative barrier factor. Change that factor modestly, and the probability multiplies by enormous powers of ten.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "decay"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.67,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Higher alpha energy shrinks the forbidden region and makes the barrier effectively thinner. The leaking tail decays less before reaching the far side, so escape becomes vastly more likely.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "split"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.77,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Polonium two-twelve emits an alpha near eight point seven eight mega electron volts and lives about three-tenths of a microsecond.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.06,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Thorium two-thirty-two emits near four point zero one mega electron volts and has a half-life near fourteen billion years. The energy is only roughly halved; the clock is transformed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.75,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Put alpha emitters on a graph of log half-life against one over the square root of energy. They line up approximately along straight families. That is the Geiger–Nuttall law, explained by tunneling.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.37,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:34:37"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "A straight line on a logarithmic plot hides a savage fact: modest nuclear-energy changes become dozens of zeros in ordinary lifetime.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.64,
